---|   USER MANUAL (v3.2)   |---
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=

--- PLAYER COMMANDS ---

1. /register
   Command: /register <password> <password> [captcha]
   Description: Registers a new account.
   Note: If Captcha is enabled, you must type the code displayed in chat.

2. /login
   Command: /login <password>
   Description: Logs you into the server.

3. /changepass
   Command: /changepass <old password> <new password> <new password>
   Description: Changes your current password.

4. /premium
   Command: /premium
   Description: Enables Auto-Login for Premium Minecraft accounts.
   How it works: The plugin verifies your account with Mojang and saves your IP.
   Future logins from this IP will skip the password check.

5. /cracked
   Command: /cracked
   Description: Disables Premium Auto-Login. You will be required to enter
   your password every time you join.

--- ADMIN COMMANDS (Permission: pureauth.admin) ---

6. /pureauth
   Command: /pureauth
   Description: Displays the list of administrative commands.

7. /pureauth unlock
   Command: /pureauth unlock <player>
   Description: Unblocks an account that was locked due to brute-force protection.
   Note: This command resets the player's failed attempt counter.

8. /pureauth forcelogin
   Command: /pureauth forcelogin <player>
   Description: Forcefully logs in an online player, bypassing password and lock checks.
   (Logs to Discord).

9. /pureauth setpassword
    Command: /pureauth setpassword <player> <new password>
    Description: Changes a player's password without needing the old one.
    (Logs to Discord).

10. /pureauth unregister
    Command: /pureauth unregister <player>
    Description: Deletes a player's account from the database.
    (Logs to Discord).

11. /pureauth register
    Command: /pureauth register <player> <password>
    Description: Manually registers an account for a player.

12. /pureauth info
    Command: /pureauth info <player>
    Description: Displays account details: Registration IP, Last Login, Premium Status, Lock Status.

13. /pureauth accounts
    Command: /pureauth accounts <IP>
    Description: Lists all usernames registered to a specific IP address.

14. /pureauth location
    Command: /pureauth location <login|register>
    Description: Sets the global teleport spawn points for unauthenticated players.

15. /pureauth reload
    Command: /pureauth reload
    Description: Reloads the configuration file and language settings.

16. /pureauth stats
    Command: /pureauth stats
    Description: [CONSOLE ONLY] Displays a technical report of the plugin status
    and active security settings.

--- SYSTEM CONFIGURATION NOTES ---

- Security: Passwords are hashed using BCrypt.
- Account Locking: By default, 3 kicks (9 wrong password attempts) will PERMANENTLY lock an account until an admin unlocks it.
- Safe Mode: If 'safe_mode: true' is set in config, sensitive commands (unregister, setpassword, etc.) are blocked in-game.
- Discord: Webhook URL must be configured in config.yml for logs to appear.

Developed by SzymeX Dev Studio.
